From cf329e7668d3b6827d1324efa96a7615782c4627 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 16:36:56 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Refactor profile README into heatmap + two-column layout

- Rework README into the target layout: snake contribution animation on
  top, then a two-column table (compact ASCII photo | terminal-style info
  box). Replace stripped inline CSS with GitHub-safe align attributes and
  a theme-aware <picture>; add a GIF placeholder and fix "Aspriring" typo.
- Scale generate.py ASCII output from 80 to 40 cols so it fits the left
  column; make background removal degrade gracefully and auto-inject the
  art into the README between markers.
- Add scripts/update_stats.py to fetch live repo/follower counts and inject
  them into the README stats block.
- Add .github/workflows/update-readme.yml (daily cron + manual + push,
  contents: write, commit & push when changed) and snake.yml to generate
  the contribution animation into the output branch.
- Trim requirements.txt, add .gitignore, drop stray empty directory.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_017DmvoY66js8XqBRqJxKQKQ
